            "notes": [
              {
                "label": "Notes",
                "content": "\" Written with version 2015.\""
              },
              {
                "label": "Notes",
                "content": "Accompanying disc contains exercises, a PDF copy of the manual, and moving image visuals with spoken commentary."
              },
              {
                "label": "Notes",
                "content": "Disc in pocket."
              },
              {
                "label": "Notes",
                "content": "\"Series VP978\"--Disc label."
              },
              {
                "label": "Contents",
                "content": "Introduction -- Simple 3D modeling -- Architectural modeling -- Bus stop project"
              },
              {
                "label": "Summary",
                "content": "\"The seventh edition Vectorworks 3D Modeling Tutorial manual is a must-have workbook for anyone seeking to learn how to free-form model with Vectorworks. Exercises aimed at building a foundation of 3D Vectorworks skills include creating 3D forms through the use of extrudes, sweeps, solids, NURBS, loft surfaces, and 3D primitives. This manual will bring you to a competent level of 3D capability.\"--Back cover."
              }
